sorcer.core.context.model.ent

Class Proc<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • sorcer.co.tuple.Tuple2<java.lang.String,T>
      • sorcer.core.context.model.ent.Entry<T>
        • sorcer.core.context.model.ent.Proc<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<T>, Arg, Call, Callable<T>, Dependency, Evaluation<T>, Identifiable, Invocation<T>, Mappable<T>, EvaluationComponent, SupportComponent, Variability<T>, Perturbation<T>, Reactive<T>, Request, Scopable, Service, Setter, Substitutable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Agent, SysCall

    public class Proc<T>
extends Entry<T>
implements Variability<T>, Mappable<T>, Invocation<T>, Setter, Scopable, java.lang.Comparable<T>, Reactive<T>
    In service-based modeling, a parameter (for short a proc) is a special kind of variable, used in a service context ProcModel to refer to one of the pieces of data provided as input to the invokers (subroutines of the context). These pieces of data are called arguments.
    Author:
    Mike Sobolewski

    Serialized Form
